## Post 2
**Date:** 1 day ago
**Topic:** $45,572 spent on LinkedIn ads — 
one rule most people skip

**Content Summary:**
Brendan's core LinkedIn ads principle:
"If a post can't earn attention organically, 
paying to distribute it just helps more people 
ignore it. Test organically. Scale with ads."

Content layering framework:
- Top layer: names the problem so they feel seen
- Next layer: shows the path out so they trust you
- Proof comes last when they are ready to believe it

Key insight:
"The average B2B buying journey is 272 days. 
You don't need one viral post. 
You need sustained presence with the right people."

**Why this matters for AI-powered SEO content production:**
Directly relevant — organic content performance 
is the filter for what gets amplified with ads. 
The same principle applies to AI content production: 
test what resonates organically before scaling 
with AI-assisted production. 
AI should scale what works — not what you hope works.

