## Post 3
**Date:** 2 days ago
**Topic:** 47% newsletter open rate — 
behind-the-scenes SaaS case studies

**Content Summary:**
Brendan's newsletter achieves 47% open rate 
and high unsolicited reply rate from CMOs and VPs 
by publishing in-depth behind-the-scenes 
case studies of winning SaaS brands — 
Figma case study example:
- Figma has 10,000+ indexed pages driving search traffic 
  — content team did not write a single one
- Two-thirds of Figma's 13 million users are not designers
- Community team does not report to the CMO

**Why this matters for AI-powered SEO content production:**
The Figma insight is critical — 10,000+ indexed pages 
produced by the community, not the content team. 
User-generated and community content at scale 
is one of the most powerful AI-visible content 
strategies because it is genuinely unique, 
authentic, and impossible to replicate with 
AI content production alone.

